{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use|4500+}}
{{Template shortcut|UCE|En-CA}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->

== Usage ==

{{Tlx|Use Canadian English|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}

This maintenance template adds articles to [[:Category:Use Canadian English]] to denote articles that have [[Canadian English]] spelling conventions. All articles chiefly concerning [[Canada]] should use Canadian English spelling conventions, consistent with the Wikipedia policy on English usage for articles about prominently English-speaking countries.

== See also ==
{{Use X English}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS HERE, THANKS -->
[[Category:Use English templates]]
[[Category:Templates with no visible output]]
}}</includeonly> 

== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "Placed near the top of an article; informs editors to use Canadian English in the article.",
	"format": "{{_|_=_}}\n",
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "The month and year that the template was placed (in full). \"May 2025\" inserts the current month and year automatically.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"example": "January 2013",
			"suggested": true
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

